    <h2 align="center">SUS!NAVpasikat 2014 – A Fundraising Project for Food for Hungry Minds School</h2><br/><hr/><br/><br/>
       
    <h3> Mechanics for the MTV:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>The groups should prepare and create a 3-5 minute Black and White MTV featuring a song and dance.</li>
        <li>The song can be Tagalog or English or it can be a Mashup music.</li>
        <li>The groups are free to choose their theme for their MTV.</li>
        <li>The groups should observe the following guidelines:
            <ul>
                <li>○ It should be wholesome and suitable for all ages</li>
                <li>○ No profanity</li>
                <li>○ No repetitive abusive language</li>
                <li>○ No nudity</li>
                <li>○ No discrimination (racial, sexual, or any other kind)</li>
                <li>○ Should observe Accenture policies</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Video should be submitted on or before November 10 (to follow- details on how to submit). </li>
        <li>Deductions will apply for late submission.</li>
       
    </ol><br/>



<h3> AWARDS:</h3>
        
    <strong>Best MTV Criteria:</strong>
    
   <pre> 
    30      Talent Showcase and Showmanship 
    30      Creativity and Originality
    15      Video Quality, Editing, Sound quality
    25      Audience Impact and Entertainment value
    -------------------------------------------
    100     Total Score   

   </pre>         

